OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775696638
OL,3,C'Extremist' Reform could replace
OL,4,CTories as opposition, veteran MSP warns
OL,6,F"When I came into Parliament under
OL,7,FDavid McLetchie, who was a fantastic
OL,8,Fleader, he did so much to sort of lay
OL,9,Fthe basis and then I think Ruth
OL,10,FDavidson came in and was able to grow
OL,11,Fthe party, she was able to grow the
OL,12,Fappeal across the electorate, not just
OL,13,Fbecause of the timing of her
OL,14,Fleadership, which is obviously very
OL,15,Fmuch related to the referendum.
OL,17,F"So, my regret is that after that time
OL,18,Fwe've seen a decline."
OL,26,@nD@AOUyD@AOUzD@VO]
